<p><strong>Last updated: April 2026</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Perplexity AI has 45 million monthly active users as of early 2026.</strong> The AI search engine processes over 780 million queries per month, generates $200 million in annual recurring revenue, and holds a valuation above $21 billion. It is the third-largest AI chatbot by market share.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Perplexity AI grew from a small startup in August 2022 to one of the most-funded AI companies in the world. It now competes directly with Google, ChatGPT, and Microsoft Copilot for search traffic.</p>
<p>If you run a website or manage SEO, these numbers affect how people find your content. AI search engines like Perplexity pull answers from web pages, cite sources inline, and change how <a href="/blog/ai-search-changing-seo/">organic traffic flows</a>.</p>
<p>In this post, we compiled 50+ Perplexity AI statistics from Similarweb, TechCrunch, Wikipedia, DemandSage, and company disclosures.</p>
<p>Here is what the data shows:</p>
<ul>
<li>Perplexity user growth, traffic, and engagement numbers</li>
<li>Query volume and how it compares to Google</li>
<li>Revenue trajectory from $5 million to $200 million ARR</li>
<li>Funding rounds totaling $1.72 billion</li>
<li>Demographics, market share, and product milestones</li>
</ul>
<h2>General Perplexity AI Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>1. Perplexity AI has 45 million monthly active users.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / Similarweb, early 2026.
That is a 350% increase from 10 million MAU in early 2024.</p>
<p><strong>2. The platform processes 780 million queries per month.</strong>
Source: Perplexity CEO Aravind Srinivas, May 2025.
For context, Google handles roughly 14 billion queries per day. Perplexity is still a fraction of that but growing fast.</p>
<p><strong>3. Perplexity AI is valued at $21.2 billion.</strong>
Source: Tracxn, early 2026 (Series E-6 round).
The company was valued at just $121 million in March 2023.</p>
<p><strong>4. Annual recurring revenue reached $200 million.</strong>
Source: Wikipedia / company reports, February 2026.
Revenue grew 40x in 2 years, from $5 million ARR in 2022.</p>
<p><strong>5. The company raised $1.72 billion in total funding across 11 rounds.</strong>
Source: Tracxn, 2026.
Key investors include Jeff Bezos, Nvidia, SoftBank, Accel, and IVP.</p>
<p><strong>6. Perplexity holds a 6.4% to 8% share of the AI chatbot market.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / FatJoe, 2026.
It ranks third behind ChatGPT (82.6%) and Microsoft Copilot (7.2%).</p>
