<h2>User and Traffic Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>7. Monthly website visits reached 170 million in early 2026.</strong>
Source: Similarweb, 2026.
Traffic peaked at 240 million monthly visits in November 2025, according to GetPanto.</p>
<p><strong>8. Perplexity had 22 million monthly active users at the start of 2025.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, January 2025.
That doubled from approximately 10 million users in early 2024.</p>
<p><strong>9. Daily active users number 2 million.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / Similarweb, 2026.
Average daily visitors are higher at 5.6 million because many visitors use the tool without accounts.</p>
<p><strong>10. Lifetime app downloads exceeded 80.5 million.</strong>
Source: GetPanto, late 2025.
Peak monthly downloads hit 15.5 million in October 2025.</p>
<p><strong>11. App downloads grew 600% year over year in Q2 2025.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, Q2 2025.
Quarterly downloads reached 2.8 million on mobile.</p>
<p><strong>12. The iOS app holds a 4.9-star rating from 76,400 reviews.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, 2025.
The Google Play version has a 4.6-star rating.</p>
<p><strong>13. Average visit duration is 4 minutes and 42 seconds.</strong>
Source: Similarweb, 2026.
Users view 3.7 pages per visit with a 31.6% bounce rate. That signals strong engagement for a search tool.</p>
<p><strong>14. Direct traffic accounts for 71.6% to 73.6% of all visits.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / Similarweb, 2026.
Organic search drives 25.4%. The high direct traffic share suggests strong brand recall.</p>
<p>Understanding these traffic patterns matters for anyone working on <a href="/glossary/answer-engine-optimization/">answer engine optimization</a>. Perplexity pulls content from the web and cites it with inline links. If your pages rank well for relevant queries, Perplexity may surface them to millions of users.</p>
