<h2>Demographics and Market Share Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>32. 60.2% of Perplexity users are male. 39.8% are female.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / Similarweb, 2026.</p>
<p><strong>33. The largest age group is 25 to 34 years old at 29.5%.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, 2026.
The second largest segment is 35 to 44 (20.2%), followed by 18 to 24 (17.8%).</p>
<p><strong>34. The United States leads with 18.8% of all users.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / Similarweb, 2026.
India follows at 15.3%, then Germany (5.3%), Russia (4.8%), and France (4%).</p>
<p><strong>35. India saw 640% user growth year over year in Q2 2025.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, Q2 2025.
A partnership with telecom provider Airtel offered free Perplexity Pro access to subscribers.</p>
<p><strong>36. 78.4% of Perplexity traffic comes from desktop devices.</strong>
Source: DemandSage / Similarweb, 2026.
Only 21.6% comes from mobile. Most users treat Perplexity as a desktop research tool.</p>
<p><strong>37. YouTube drives 56.9% of social referral traffic.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, 2026.
Facebook accounts for 9% and WhatsApp for 8.9%.</p>
<p><strong>38. ChatGPT holds 82.6% of the AI chatbot market.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, 2026.
Microsoft Copilot sits at 7.2%. Perplexity ranks third at 6.4% to 8%.</p>
<p><strong>39. Perplexity captures 6.2% to 6.6% of the AI search market.</strong>
Source: FatJoe, 2025-2026.
Google still controls roughly 89.5% of overall search. But AI-specific search is a separate and growing category.</p>
