<h2>Product and Company Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>40. Perplexity AI was founded in August 2022 by 4 co-founders.</strong>
Source: Wikipedia.
Aravind Srinivas (CEO), Denis Yarats, Johnny Ho, and Andy Konwinski built the company in San Francisco.</p>
<p><strong>41. The search engine launched publicly on December 7, 2022.</strong>
Source: Wikipedia.
It reached 2 million unique visitors by February 2023, just 2 months later.</p>
<p><strong>42. Perplexity Pro costs $20 per month.</strong>
Source: Perplexity Help Center.
Pro users get access to GPT-5.2, Claude Sonnet 4.6, and Gemini 3.1 Pro models.</p>
<p><strong>43. The Max plan costs $200 per month.</strong>
Source: Perplexity Help Center.
It includes $50 in monthly API credits and priority access to all models.</p>
<p><strong>44. Enterprise pricing starts at $40 per user per month.</strong>
Source: Perplexity Enterprise.
Enterprise customers get access to 20 frontier AI models.</p>
<p><strong>45. Perplexity launched its Comet web browser in July 2025.</strong>
Source: Wikipedia.
Initially a premium feature, it became publicly available in October 2025. Comet Enterprise launched in March 2026.</p>
<p><strong>46. The Publishers' Program launched in July 2024.</strong>
Source: Wikipedia.
This revenue-sharing program addresses copyright concerns by compensating publishers whose content Perplexity cites.</p>
<p><strong>47. Multiple major publishers have filed copyright lawsuits against Perplexity.</strong>
Source: Wikipedia.
Plaintiffs include The New York Times, Dow Jones, BBC, and Reddit.</p>
<p><strong>48. Employee count grew from 52 (2024) to an estimated 200 to 500 (2025-2026).</strong>
Source: Wikipedia / LinkedIn.
Some third-party trackers estimate up to 1,600 employees across 6 continents. The exact number remains unclear.</p>
<p><strong>49. The overall year-over-year growth rate reached 800%.</strong>
Source: DemandSage, 2025-2026.
That accounts for combined user, revenue, and query growth metrics.</p>
<p><strong>50. Comet Enterprise customers include Fortune, AWS, and Bessemer Venture Partners.</strong>
Source: Perplexity Blog, March 2026.
The enterprise product bundles AI search with browser-based workflow tools.</p>
